         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/5/79. ¶ Could you, dear Sir Joseph, not lend us your  ¶ powerful ¶  aid in getting seeds of the "Coapim" ¶  Panicum spectabile? ¶  You may have thought, that we  ¶ had ¶  it in Australia, but I nev...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.05.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Brazil, Cultural Products Etc., 1852-1908, Miscellaneous Reports 16.5 (MR/759), f. 230.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/5/79.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated at top of letter</seg>:<seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>
                     <name key="Panicum%20spectabile%20">Panicum spectabile </name>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">and to left of central margin </seg>Caapim de Angola | <name key="Panicum%20spectabile%20">Panicum spectabile </name>| Oplismenus spectabilis | Palm House | Brasil - Glaz[ion] Nov 12/79.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Could you, dear Sir Joseph, not lend us your <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">powerful</hi>
               </seg> aid in getting seeds of the "Coapim"<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M uses the spelling ‘Coapim’ in B85.13.26; modern <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Brazilian spelling is ‘capim’.</p>
               </note> Panicum spectabile?<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">f. 231 in this volume is a draft letter, unsigned, dated Royal Gardens Kew September 11, 1880</seg>: Sir <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I am sending you a bag of seed of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Panicum spectabile</seg> a tropical fodder grass which is much cultivated in Brazil where it is stated to yield the best and most copious produce of any. It is a native of Angola whence it was introduced into Brazil by the Portuguese who know it as ‘Caapim de Angola.’ It grows from six to seven feet high.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">f. 232 is a sheet of rough notepaper on which W. Thiselton-Dyer(?) <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has written</seg>: <name key="Panicum%20spectabile%20">Panicum spectabile </name>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Half to Baron von Mueller <seg style="font-style: italic; ">followed by a list of fifteen places or people</seg>.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 26 November 1880.</p>
               </note> You may have thought, that we <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">had</hi>
               </seg> it in Australia, but I never yet saw here or elsewhere a living plant. What the Adelaide bot. Garden for several years has sent out as P. spectabile is merely the Cuba-grass, <name key="Andropogon%20Haleppensis">Andropogon Haleppensis</name>,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">A. halepensis?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> praised since Theophrastos time, i.e. nearly 2000 years, and cultivated by me since 1858. It is a good grass also, but apt to spread in cultivation like Agropyrum repens. Had I been left in my Directorship all these things could have been attended to also.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I wrote latterly to Dr Kirk of Zanzibar<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">John Kirk. Letter not found.</p>
               </note> for the seeds of the P. spectabile, but he may not have it on the eastern side of Africa.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your splendid plate of <name key="Euchlaena%20luxurians%20">Euchlaena luxurians </name>gives a good idea of this noble grass.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">Hooker (1865-1904),</seg> vol. 105, pl. 6414. There is a sideline in the central margin of the letter beside this passage.</p>
               </note> I had seeds 3 years ago from Bourbon<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Réunion, Indian Ocean.</p>
               </note> &amp; from Paris, and two years ago it bore immensely at Muellersville, poor Thozet’s place, from whence it is gone over all the warmer parts of Australia. Here we must keep it under glass.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Agropyrum%20repens%20">Agropyrum repens </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Andropogon%20Haleppensis">Andropogon Haleppensis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Euchlaena%20luxurians%20">Euchlaena luxurians </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Panicum%20spectabile%20">Panicum spectabile </name>
            </p>
         </div>
